         <div id="leftcol">
            <h3><img src="/pix/computerman-banner8.jpg" /></h3>
<h1>About VitalSource<sup>TM</sup></h1>

<div id="bookshelf_left">
   <h2>The business of digital publishing</h2>
   <p>VitalSource<sup>TM</sup> was founded in 1994 with a vision for moving resource access into the digital age. For more than a decade, we have been helping
      <a href="/about/publishers/">publishers</a> and <a href="/about/thenewstudent/">learners</a> find new, mutually beneficial business relationships.
   </p>
   <p>We concentrate on ways the computer can enhance learning, and particularly on how computers
      can aid in the delivery and use of trusted, respected resources in the classroom.
      To this end, we have developed the world's most successful downloadable digital book format: the <a href="/software/vbk/">VitalBook<sup>TM</sup></a>.
   </p>
</div>

<div id="bookshelf_right">
   <p>Today, VitalSource<sup>TM</sup> works with many of the largest and best known <a href="/about/publishers/">publishers</a>
      in the world (as well as with some of the largest and best known computer manufacturers in the world) to
      establish successful digital curriculum implementations. These implementations can currently be found in
      K-12, Higher Ed, and Professional Education in countries around the globe.<br />
   </p>
   <p>Working closely with academic institutions, VitalSource<sup>TM</sup> has invested years of research and development to
      create tools that 1) help learners be more successful, 2) save educators time and money, and 3) help
      publishers secure new business in worldwide education's emerging digital market.<br />
   </p>
</div>

